Both required files emitted in the bundle directory.

- `transcript.json` — 25 iterations, 28 hypotheses, 28 analyses; validates against `transcript_schema.json`.
- `analysis_summary.txt` — narrative synthesis covering main effects, multivariable model (R² = 0.858), interactions, and the demographic-equity findings (no race or insurance disparity in pfs_months).

Headline findings: pfs_months is dominated by feature_078 (Spearman ρ = +0.785), feature_057 (ordinal, PS-like, monotonic decrease 5.27→2.91 mo), feature_051 (binary, −1.35 mo), and feature_038 (binary, +0.97 mo). Notable interactions: feature_078 × feature_051 (slope attenuation, p ≈ 2e-9), feature_078 × feature_057 (ceiling at level 2, p ≈ 7e-23), and feature_013 × feature_043 (sub-additive, p ≈ 1e-25). Race (feature_064) and insurance (feature_018) showed no main effect (p = 0.48, 0.22) and no significant interaction with feature_051; adding demographics to the clinical model raised R² by < 1e-5.
